columns.text:
a. The income statement equation can be denoted in three ways:
&nbsp;
$$\begin{aligned}
\textbf{Gross Profit}& = \text{Revenues - Cost of Goods Sold} \\ \\
\end{aligned}$$

$$\begin{aligned}
\textbf{Operating Income}& = \text{Gross Profit - Operating expenses} \\ \\
\end{aligned}$$

$$\begin{aligned}
\textbf{Net Income}& = \text{Operating Income + Non-operating items} \\ \\
\end{aligned}$$
